**Item:** SCP-8554

**Containment Class:** Uncontained

**Containment Protocols:** Item 8554 has not been successfully contained as of the date of this document. Mobile Task Force Kappa-20 ("The Collectors") has been assigned to the location and apprehension of Item 8554. All Foundation personnel who encounter Item 8554 in the field are prohibited from making physical contact with the Item under any circumstances, and must maintain a minimum distance of five metres at all times. Sightings of Item 8554 must be reported to MTF Kappa-20 immediately.

Upon successful apprehension, Item 8554 is to be transferred to a designated humanoid containment chamber at Facility 04.

**Description:** Item 8554 is a human male of Hispanic descent, approximately 20 to 25 years of age, standing approximately 175 cm in height. Both of the Item's hands are absent of dermal and muscular tissue from the wrist distally, exposing the underlying osseous and tendinous structures. Despite the absence of musculature, full range of motion in both hands is retained. The words "Mr. Bone, from Little Misters ® by Dr. Wondertainment" is tattooed on the Item's right forearm.

Item 8554's primary anomalous property consists of the capacity to induce immediate and complete extraction of osseous tissue from any living organism upon direct physical contact, resulting in structural collapse of the affected subject. The mechanism by which this extraction occurs remains undetermined. Application of this property appears to be voluntary.
Item 8554 is also documented to possess a secondary property consisting of the capacity to accelerate osseous tissue repair and reinforcement in living organisms upon direct physical contact. The extent and limitations of this property have not been fully established.

At the time of initial identification, Item 8554was wearing a grey hooded sweatshirt and denim trousers, with 'Doctor's Orders' sewn into all garment tags, alongside its corresponding Little Mister list (see Document 8554/A).

**Addendum I:** Discovery 

On 03/04/2023, Foundation analysts intercepted a message addressed to Site-19 command, originating from an unknown sender and bearing the signature of Dr. Wondertainment. The message contained the geographic coordinates of a location in São Miguel dos Milagres, Alagoas, Brazil, accompanied by the following text:
[[div class="blockquote" style="border: solid 1px #999999; background: white; text-align: justify;"]]
To the Wonderful People at the Foundation, I write this Wondrous Message.
I trust you are keeping well, all things considered. I will spare us both the pleasantries — you know who I am, and I suspect you know by now that when I reach out, it is worth your time to listen.

I am writing to bring to your attention a small institute operating out of  São Miguel dos Milagres, Brazil, by the name of Árida Labs. I expect it has escaped your notice — it is, frankly, beneath it. Small, quiet, and largely unremarkable; the sort of place that exists precisely because nobody thinks to look twice. I, however, have found reason to look, and I think you will agree the results are illuminating.

The coordinates are enclosed. I recommend prompt action — the locals are beginning to ask inconvenient questions, and I suspect the answers will interest you considerably more than them.

— //W//
[[/div]]

Foundation personnel were dispatched to the coordinates on 24/04/2023, where they discovered seventeen casualties on the premises of Árida Labs, a privately-operated biological research institute located in São Miguel dos Milagres, Brazil. All subjects presented identical conditions: complete absence of osseous tissue, with dermal and muscular structures intact and otherwise undamaged. Subsequent investigation determined that Árida Labs had been operating under anomalous conditions for approximately three years prior to the incident, though the scale of its operations was significantly smaller than comparable organizations of interest. All records pertaining to the incident and the institute's anomalous activities were subsequently suppressed by Foundation personnel, except for he information regarding the possible causes of the deaths of the individuals working at Árida Labs.

Cross-referencing the incident with intelligence obtained during the investigation of Whateley Biotech confirmed the involvement of an anomalous entity consistent with the description provided by Oswald Whateley during his interview on 15/05/2023 (see [https://scp-wiki.wikidot.com/scp-8942 SCP-8942], Addendum V). Such entity was subsequently designated as Item 8554.

The origin and authenticity of the intercepted message remain under investigation. Cryptographic analysis determined that the message's cipher, though elementary in construction, went undetected by four separate Foundation analytical teams for a period of eleven days prior to its decryption. The circumstances surrounding this delay are considered anomalous.

