[[=]]
**External Examination**
[[/=]]
Decedent is an adult male of approximately 35 to 40 years of age. **Height:** 178 cm. **Weight:** 31 kg, significantly below expected range for recorded height. Dermal tissue is intact across all surfaces with no lacerations, contusions, or signs of external trauma. Skin texture and coloration present no abnormalities consistent with conventional cause of death. No defensive wounds are present.
----
[[=]]
**Internal Examination**
[[/=]]
Complete absence of osseous tissue is confirmed throughout the entirety of the skeletal structure. Muscular, connective, and organ tissue are intact and undamaged, retaining normal structural appearance. No hemorrhaging, necrosis, or cellular degradation consistent with conventional osseous disease or trauma is observed. The mechanism by which osseous tissue was extracted without damage to surrounding tissue is undetermined.

Cause of death is attributed to acute structural collapse of the thoracic cavity, resulting in compression of cardiac and pulmonary tissue. Time of death is estimated at 48 to 72 hours prior to examination.
-----
[[=]]
**Conclusion**
[[/=]]
No conventional cause consistent with the observed conditions has been identified. The complete and atraumatic extraction of osseous tissue across all skeletal structures is assessed as anomalous in origin. Findings are consistent across all seventeen casualties recovered from the Árida Labs premises. Further investigation is recommended.

Samples retained for anomalous analysis: muscle tissue (8554-BR-01-M), connective tissue (8554-BR-01-C).
[[/cell]]
[[/row]]
